 The Taraba State Police Command has confirmed the killing of five persons including two village heads in Muri chiefdom, under Karim-Lamido Local Government Area. Spokesperson for the command, David Misal, confirmed the incident to SaharaReporters, saying, "We are aware of the incident but no arrest has been made yet." A resident, Sunday Danladi, told our correspondent that the gunmen invaded Bilango 1  and  Bilango 2 communities in Muri chiefdom on Tuesday evening. He said, "The bandits were about 30 in number, armed with AK47 rifles and claimed they were on a reprisal to avenge the killing of some of their members. "Garba Dangari and Sarki Ali are the two village heads killed by the gunmen."